        public void postEvent​(double cTime,
                      double time,
                      TimeUnits tu)
        Description copied from interface: EventQueueWriteable
        Post an TimeEvent to an class (EventTimer). The time will be converted to the classe's time units (aka the Shortest time unit of the timeline). An exception is thrown if, after conversion, the currentTime < time. We need to test the case of currentTime==time. Maybe this can be allowed
